snippet.textDisplay:
QNED - Quantum dot + Nanorod lED
Nanorod LEDs are inorganic miniLEDs shaped like a rod (most probably a GaN Nanorod) 
Quantum dots basically absorb the blue light coming from the Nanorod LED and re-emits red, blue, green/yellow lights. They are like the substitute for color filters in LCD display. Since filters block some wavelengths of light, most of the incoming energy is lost. Quantum dots, on the other hand, reemit most of the absorbed energy in the required wavelength. Quantum dots are theoretically more efficient (light's color is determined by its wavelength).
